## FAQ

### Is it okay to use AI to write customer emails?

**Yes, but with conditions.** Use AI to draft responses, but always review, edit, and personalize before sending. The final message should feel like it came from you, not AI. Never send fully AI-written messages without human review.

<Checklist>
<ChecklistItem id="ai-email-1">Use AI for drafting and structure</ChecklistItem>
<ChecklistItem id="ai-email-2">Always review and personalize before sending</ChecklistItem>
<ChecklistItem id="ai-email-3">Maintain your authentic voice and tone</ChecklistItem>
<ChecklistItem id="ai-email-4">Never send fully automated responses without human oversight</ChecklistItem>
</Checklist>

### How do I know if I've over-automated?

**Warning signs:** Declining customer satisfaction, more requests for human support, lower engagement, negative feedback mentioning "robotic" or "impersonal" interactions. Track connection metrics (CSAT, NPS), not just efficiency metrics.

### Should I tell customers when they're talking to AI?

**Yes, always.** Transparency builds trust. People accept automation when they know what to expect. They feel deceived when AI pretends to be human. Simple language like "This is an automated message—III'llapos;llapos;ll respond personally within 24 hours" works well.

<Callout title="Pro Tip">
Being transparent about automation actually increases trust. Customers appreciate honesty and are more forgiving when they know what to expect.
</Callout>

### What's the biggest mistake businesses make with automation?

**Over-automating high-touch interactions.** Automating sales outreach, customer complaints, or complex support issues signals "You're not worth my time." These moments require authentic human connection. Automate the routine, preserve the relational.

### Can small businesses compete without heavy automation?

**Absolutely.** In fact, small businesses have an advantage: you can be more personal and human than big companies. Use automation to handle routine tasks, freeing you to provide exceptional, personalized service that big competitors can't match.

<Callout title="Small Business Advantage">
Your size is your strength! While big companies struggle with bureaucracy and impersonal service, you can leverage automation to provide the efficiency of a large company with the personal touch of a small one.
</Callout>

